   <row>
    <id><![CDATA[11806]]></id>
    <qid><![CDATA[11806]]></qid>
    <question><![CDATA[<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:26px;"><big>CONSENT FORM</big></span></h1><h1><br /><span style="font-size:26px;"><big>RESEARCH TITLE: Improvements to User Interfaces of video games to enhance player experience</big></span></h1><p> </p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:20px;">I provide consent to the responsible researcher</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:20px;"><i><em class="textItalic">Vikramaditya Thakur, Master Game Technology Student, Breda University of Applied Science</em></i></span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:20px;">to use my data within the above-mentioned project.</span></p><p><span style="font-size:20px;"> </span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:20px;">I have been informed about the research project entitled ‘</span><strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Improvements to User Interfaces of video games to enhance player experience</span></strong><span style="font-size:20px;">’ and have been requested to provide personal information and fill out questionnaires, by the researcher.</span></p><p><span style="font-size:20px;">  </span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:20px;">I have been informed about the goal of this project and I have had the opportunity to ask the researcher any questions which may arise about the research and my participation.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:20px;">  </span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:20px;">I have been informed that the game I am about to play includes playable situations related to intense violence, family conflict, hostage situation, and other mature themes, which might be uncomfortable for me, and I am free to stop participating in the study at any given time. </span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:20px;"> </span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:20px;">I understand that my participation in this research is voluntary, and I am free to refuse to participate and free to withdraw from the research at any time.<br /> <br />I have also been informed that if I choose to stop participating or withdraw after completing the experiment, my responses will be permanently deleted from the database.</span><br /><span style="font-size:20px;"> <br /><span class="fontstyle0">I have been made aware that the data is to be handled only by the responsible researcher prior to full anonymization. All data presented outside of the researcher will be presented in an anonymized way.</span><br /> </span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:20px;">If I have any enquiries about the research or any concerns or complaints regarding the way the research is or has been conducted, I can contact <strong>Vikramaditya Thakur (232979@buas.nl)</strong>, the responsible researcher.</span></p>]]></question>
    <help/>
    <language><![CDATA[en]]></language>
   </row>
   <row>
    <id><![CDATA[11807]]></id>
    <qid><![CDATA[11807]]></qid>
    <question><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-size:20px;"><span class="fontstyle0">By Accepting below, I am indicating my consent to:</span></span></p><ul>	<li><span style="font-size:20px;"><span class="fontstyle0">Provide personal information and data through questionnaires regarding your experience during </span><span class="fontstyle0">the experiment.</span></span></li>	<li><span style="font-size:20px;"><span class="fontstyle0">Having the collected data used to evaluate the problems with User Interfaces of video games.</span></span></li>	<li><span style="font-size:20px;"><span class="fontstyle0">Being contacted if further clarification is necessary to investigate statements present in the </span><span class="fontstyle0">collected data.</span></span><br /> </li></ul><p><span style="font-size:20px;"><span class="fontstyle0">I understand that the data collected from my participation will be used for the purpose of this research and will be securely stored, and I consent for it to be used in that manner.</span></span></p>]]></question>
    <help/>
    <language><![CDATA[en]]></language>
   </row>
